body.name: Gamdias RGB Gaming ATX Mid Tower Computer PC Case with Side Tempered Glass Panel and a Magnetic Dust Filter & 3 Built-in 120mm ARGB Fans
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Friday, February 16. Order within 5 hrs
features: The TALOS E3 is a premium compact mid-tower case with an elegant snowy white outlook. Featuring 3 built-in 120mm ARGB fans, tempered glasses on both the front and side panel, and a PSU cover design for a minimalist design.
A CLEAN OUTLOOK : The case is equipped with 3 built-in 120mm ARGB fans displayed by tempered glass front and side panels.
PSU SHROUD DESIGN : Building upon the inner beauty of the case, a vented power supply shroud at the bottom of the case surrounds the PSU and perfectly hides the cables.
Panoramic Tempered Glass Every artwork should be seen. Display your internal rig with the 4mm tinted panoramic tempered glass side panel. Let the masterpiece astonish whole planet!
ONE CLICK. SYNC ALL : TALOS E3 supports ARGB connection to compatible motherboards in order to achieve system-wide lighting synchronization, making it easier to unite the case from chaos to calm.
body.description: GAMDIAS is a world-renowned global manufacturer of high-quality gaming peripherals and technologies. We specialize in creating premium peripherals, components, and furniture for all gamers, pc enthusiasts, and virtual influencers to excel and perform at their best.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About Us GAMDIAS Technology was founded in 2012 by a team of gaming enthusiasts envisioning each of our products to contain the distinct characteristics of the gods in Greek Mythology. The first three letters GAM represents the fundamental essence of our drive, thus our slogan “Gaming Art in Motion”; and the latter four words DIAS is the Latin word for god. Lastly, creating a classical golden inverted triangle logo that contains the intent of the king of gods━ZEUS━to represent the unyielding spirit of every gamer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars incredible for the value
reviews.reviewText: This is an amazing case for the value, let alone you get the fans too! Now they aren't the highest of quality but their still pretty amazing and quiet. The case alone is actually really well designed, with plenty of room in plenty of area's for allowing you to fill out the case with the parts you desire. I was pretty impressed as I'm used to Lian Li or Corsair cases, so seeing this being so well constructed was kinda impressive knowing a paid a quarter of what some of those cost. It was the base to a computer for my child, and both of us are quite happy with the latest gaming rig.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 4, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars PC Builder of 30 years - Sold my In-Win 303, the tried this case and LOVE the change!
reviews.reviewText: I used to think people who tricked out their computers were OCD overachievers. But now in my later years, sitting in my dark office, I never tire of watching my Apollo spinning orbs under my desk.. reminding that I am indeed a master builder of 30 years.The case is sturdy enough. It is light enough. There is room enough for any board, though I highly recommend an m-ATX board size to give you better choices for wire routing.The glass door on a hinge is smart (entire door can be removed).. and I like the magnetic pull lever to open it. Glass front is a change of pace and enhances the frontal lighting. Please note the stickers on the fans are NOT perfectly centered and when the fans spin, they create a wobble-illusion. I actually LIKE this effect. (The fans are centered properly, it's an illusion)My work office is whisper quiet and I do hear the fans if I listen intently, but they are more a hushed whisper. Quiet freaks will be satisfied.Venting and wire routing is perfect, the display vents for the PSU and fan mount options all work for me, but honestly in this model, other than the CPU fan, it's silly to add more fans than what comes with the case.I am also new to ARGB.. and this was the first time I took advantage. With eight color choices at the touch of a button, what is there not to love? (My fav is aqua) Make sure your board has the dedicated '2 pin- empty gap-1 pin' special ARGB headers or you will NOT get the multi lighting benefits. DO NOT TRY TO FIT THESE INTO ANY OTHER HEADER or you will blow circuits.Trap door overhanging the rear PCIe slots was new to me.. and it took me a few moments to figure out that you just twist the knob-screw retainer and swing it out.I paid $63 for the case when it was on sale and I would pay more to buy it again. The price is excellent. The ARGB fans alone are worth quite a bit (keep that in mind when case shopping.)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars I would highly recommend this case
reviews.reviewText: I purchased the ATX Mid Tower Case and for the most part I'm very happy.PROS:* It's wide and long enough to fit my RTX 3090* It looks great* Class doors and front work greatCONS:* Fans aren't silent. They're not loud or obnoxious, but you can definitely hear them* Not the best airflow out the box. Both front and back fans are setup to pull, so there is not push-pull action. Not a huge deal. You can always flip the back fan if needed.I would highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good and Sturdy case.
reviews.reviewText: This came in 3 days early. For the build I put in a Ryzen 7 2700x and RX 580. I got this for $50 which is a very good deal for how sturdy and expensive the case feels.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Plenty of space, quiet, and gorgeous!
reviews.reviewText: I was hoping that by going with big fans I wouldn't hear them and this case did not disappoint! I have to put an ear about 3 inches (8 cm) from the fans to hear anything at all. I appreciated the customizability of this case. I could fit a large video card (ARC 770) easily and I knew it'd fit beforehand because the dimensions were clearly defined on the market page. I was able to remove parts I didn't need with ease and the whole thing still feels solid. I love the big window so I can easily see the innards of my system (and the colors). There's lots of pass-through spaces on the motherboard mount to pass cables through to keep things looking nice and neat. I think this is my favorite case I've ever had and I've been building systems since the 90's. Very nice!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very clean look and has a good amount of space for basic to mid range parts, lots of ssd slots

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Worth the price but needs extra fans for top
reviews.reviewText: Got this case mainly for the fans on the front but there's not really enough clearance to make them much more than cosmetic. But other than that it's a good case with solid construction. All and all I'd recommend it for a budget bulid

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My first PC
reviews.reviewText: It looks awesome but goddam is it noisy. It also might be because it’s next to me but in all honesty i think it’s great and not as bad as reviews/reddit say. My 7800x3d and 7800XT don't seem to have any problems and perform as expected.

reviews.reviewTitle: Very good product, but why SATA to power front fans?
reviews.reviewText: This is a good PC case overall and it is cheap with plenty of room. It has vertical GPU mounting too which is very useful and the fans are big and quiet. They look good with ARGB colors on. I did not like the fact the front fans connect directly to the PSU with SATA connector as it makes them uncontrollable for the MB.

Das Gehäuse ist soweit gut verarbeitet. Für den Preis auf jeden Fall sehr gut. Einzig die Frontlüfter, welche aufgrund der Größe eigentlich sehr gut sind und laufruhig sein sollten, können von der Drehzahl her nicht geregelt werden. Lediglich die LEDs sind ARGB - lassen sich also sehr einfach in eine vorhandene Steuerung integrieren. Die elektrische Konstruktion der Lüfter lässt leider auch keine Änderungen / Umbau für eine Drehzahlregelung vor - sehr schade.
Très bon boîtier manque de ventilateurs

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great Case. Had no problems with cooling.....Visually appealing and looks better than I ever expected. As its a small case, cable management was a tad more difficult, but nothing to worry about. Highly Recommend if you're building on a budget!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on July 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: Excellent computer case with a sleek design
reviews.reviewText: Excellent case easy to open and access all components. The glass door that opens via hinges is great. I was able to put my GTX 3070 card of 30cm without problem but be careful it is the max limit. I also put a double ventilation Air Cooling that installs and integrates easily. I changed the front fans because I wanted to connect them to my motherboard because the original connectors are not compatible with the motherboard connectors. But this is just a personal choice because the original fans are good quality and quiet.
